      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This feeling of being a burden can be incredibly heavy, but it rarely reflects the reality that your children observe every day. They know you are hurting and doing your best to protect them even when things feel messy, and love is often the strongest antidote to self-doubt. I encourage you to listen to a parent support resource or counselor who can help reframe these thoughts so you see their future bright rather than dimmed by your fears. Please know that seeking help to alleviate that pain is just an act of love, however small it seems in the moment.",
